# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Claude Authentication (pick ONE)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OPTION A: Claude Pro/Max subscription (recommended if you already have one)
#   Your OAuth credentials are automatically mounted from ~/.claude/.credentials.json
#   No action needed here — just make sure you've logged in on your host:
#     claude
#   and completed the browser login flow.
#
# OPTION B: API key (pay-per-use, separate from Pro/Max subscription)
#   Get one at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#   Requires prepaid API credits: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/billing
#   Uncomment and fill in:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your_key_here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub Authentication (DEPRECATED — use .claude.env per repo instead)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN here applies globally to ALL repos launched with claude-here.
# For fine-grained PATs scoped to individual repos, create a .claude.env
# file in each repo's root directory instead. See .claude.env.example.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
